1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:02,711
- [GUNSHOTS]
- [GROANS]

2
00:00:02,794 --> 00:00:05,755
<i>Dad! Dad!</i>

3
00:00:05,839 --> 00:00:07,841
<i>Men! Evacuate the hostages!</i>
<i>Let's move!</i>

4
00:00:07,924 --> 00:00:09,592
<i>- </i>[POLICE] <i>Move! Move!</i>
<i>- Let's get out of here.</i>

5
00:00:09,676 --> 00:00:10,844
[SHOUTS]

6
00:00:10,927 --> 00:00:12,637
<i>- Ah!</i>
- [GUN CLATTERS]

7
00:00:12,721 --> 00:00:14,514
[BOTH GRUNTING]

8
00:00:14,597 --> 00:00:16,641
- [BLOWS LANDING]
<i>- Ugh! Ah!</i>

9
00:00:17,225 --> 00:00:18,643
[GRUNTS]

10
00:00:18,727 --> 00:00:20,895
- [THWACKS]
- [GROANS]

11
00:00:21,354 --> 00:00:22,689
[GUNSHOTS]

12
00:00:22,772 --> 00:00:25,275
[PANTING] <i>Where's Mama?</i>
<i>And the other hostages?</i>

13
00:00:25,358 --> 00:00:26,526
<i>They were already evacuated.</i>

14
00:00:26,609 --> 00:00:30,947
<i>Sir Mike, Ms. Minnie, and their daughter</i>
<i>are probably still here.</i>

15
00:00:31,448 --> 00:00:34,534
[CABRAL] <i>Alert all men.</i>
<i>We need to arrest Greta Roja.</i>

16
00:00:34,617 --> 00:00:36,661
<i>- Why?</i>
<i>- She can't escape.</i>

17
00:00:36,745 --> 00:00:40,165
<i>Captain Jericho Jacinto</i>
<i>identified Greta Roja</i>

18
00:00:40,248 --> 00:00:43,752
<i>as the mastermind of the hostage taking</i>
<i>that took place at La Playa Roja.</i>

19
00:00:43,835 --> 00:00:47,088
<i>According to Jacinto,</i>
<i>they have evidence to support this claim.</i>

20
00:00:47,756 --> 00:00:49,424
<i>Mrs. Greta Roja, you have to come with us.</i>

21
00:00:49,507 --> 00:00:50,467
<i>Why?</i>

22
00:00:50,550 --> 00:00:54,304
<i>You have been identified as the mastermind</i>
<i>behind the La Playa Roja hostage taking.</i>

23
00:00:54,387 --> 00:00:56,264
<i>- That's not true.</i>
- [OFFICER] <i>We have evidence.</i>

24
00:00:56,347 --> 00:00:57,557
[JACINTO IN VIDEO]
<i>Don't worry.</i>

25
00:00:58,933 --> 00:01:01,186
<i>Mr. Roja, the evidence is clear.</i>

26
00:01:01,269 --> 00:01:04,355
<i>Your wife is the mastermind</i>
<i>behind the hostage taking.</i>

27
00:01:04,439 --> 00:01:07,984
<i>Shouldn't we focus first on arresting</i>
<i>the people who took us hostage?</i>

28
00:01:08,068 --> 00:01:09,652
<i>We're just following orders, Olsen.</i>

29
00:01:09,736 --> 00:01:11,946
<i>If your wife is really involved</i>
<i>in all this,</i>

30
00:01:12,030 --> 00:01:13,698
<i>it's possible that you are too.</i>

31
00:01:13,782 --> 00:01:16,451
<i>- No! No! I don't want to!</i>
<i>- Let's go, ma'am.</i>

32
00:01:22,540 --> 00:01:24,417
Why are you looking at me like that?

33
00:01:24,501 --> 00:01:26,878
Don't tell me you believe them.

34
00:01:26,961 --> 00:01:28,963
Emil Padua said

35
00:01:30,256 --> 00:01:34,344
Jacinto asked them not to hurt anyone

36
00:01:34,427 --> 00:01:36,262
except for one person.

37
00:01:37,764 --> 00:01:39,182
Me.

38
00:01:39,265 --> 00:01:41,434
[CAMERA SHUTTERS CLICKING]

39
00:01:46,189 --> 00:01:52,904
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

40
00:02:09,504 --> 00:02:12,215
No one else would do that, Greta.

41
00:02:12,298 --> 00:02:13,508
Only you.

42
00:02:14,592 --> 00:02:18,680
Why would I have the guests held hostage?

43
00:02:18,763 --> 00:02:20,014
[WENDY] Why?

44
00:02:20,974 --> 00:02:22,225
Because of money!

45
00:02:23,059 --> 00:02:26,855
Like before, you need money again!

46
00:02:26,938 --> 00:02:29,983
My husband and my son were almost killed!

47
00:02:30,066 --> 00:02:31,818
You think I'd order that to happen?!

48
00:02:32,527 --> 00:02:35,613
Emil Padua has a personal grudge
against you.

49
00:02:36,698 --> 00:02:38,825
As the mastermind, you didn't know that?!

50
00:02:40,952 --> 00:02:44,581
You dragged me and my son into this!

51
00:02:44,664 --> 00:02:47,917
My father died because of you!

52
00:02:49,752 --> 00:02:52,797
- You monster!
- [GRETA GROANS]

53
00:02:52,881 --> 00:02:54,465
[POLICE] Rowena.

54
00:02:54,549 --> 00:02:57,635
I thought you were my friend!
How could you do this?!

55
00:02:57,719 --> 00:03:01,139
- That's enough! Enough!
- How could you do this to us?!

56
00:03:01,848 --> 00:03:04,976
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

57
00:03:08,813 --> 00:03:13,693
If you are innocent, Ma,
then you have nothing to fear.

58
00:03:13,776 --> 00:03:15,904
I didn't do anything!

59
00:03:15,987 --> 00:03:17,822
What, you believe them too?

60
00:03:17,906 --> 00:03:19,741
[GRETA BREATHING SHAKILY]

61
00:03:20,366 --> 00:03:23,202
I'm asking you! Do you believe them?!

62
00:03:23,286 --> 00:03:29,167
[GRETA CRYING]

63
00:03:30,835 --> 00:03:31,878
No.

64
00:03:36,424 --> 00:03:38,718
No! It's not true!

65
00:03:38,801 --> 00:03:40,929
- [JOURNALIST 1] Mrs. Roja!
- [JOURNALIST 2] Mrs. Roja!

66
00:03:41,012 --> 00:03:43,723
How do you respond
to Captain Jacinto's accusations?

67
00:03:43,806 --> 00:03:46,851
A video has surfaced
clearly showing your involvement!

68
00:03:46,935 --> 00:03:49,103
Everyone's question is, why did you do it?

69
00:03:49,729 --> 00:03:52,232
Mrs. Roja, please answer our questions.

70
00:03:52,315 --> 00:03:53,399
The video is clear.

71
00:03:53,483 --> 00:03:54,859
- You're the mastermind.
- All units!

72
00:03:54,943 --> 00:03:57,487
- [GRETA SCREAMS, CRYING]
- Emil Padua is in the elevator.

73
00:03:57,570 --> 00:03:58,863
- Mrs. Roja!
- Ma, wait!

74
00:03:58,947 --> 00:04:02,951
- [GRETA CRYING]
- Ma! Ma!

75
00:04:06,829 --> 00:04:10,583
[GRETA CRYING HYSTERICALLY]

76
00:04:10,667 --> 00:04:11,793
Ma!

77
00:04:12,293 --> 00:04:18,383
[CRYING, WHIMPERING]

78
00:04:37,443 --> 00:04:44,242
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

79
00:05:13,938 --> 00:05:18,901
- [GRUNTING]
- [SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

80
00:05:37,795 --> 00:05:38,671
There's blood.

81
00:05:40,423 --> 00:05:41,674
Calling all units.

82
00:05:41,758 --> 00:05:44,218
Emil Padua and his men are on the stairs
leading to the basement.

83
00:05:44,302 --> 00:05:45,219
Come on!

84
00:05:45,303 --> 00:05:46,554
Move, move, move!

85
00:05:46,637 --> 00:05:52,643
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

86
00:05:58,274 --> 00:06:00,443
[LIGHT FLICKERING]

87
00:06:09,368 --> 00:06:16,292
- [FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]
- [GRUNTING, BREATHING HEAVILY]

88
00:06:31,849 --> 00:06:32,892
[GOON] I think this is it.

89
00:06:34,227 --> 00:06:35,103
[MIKE] Yes.

90
00:06:35,686 --> 00:06:37,271
That's the sewage line.

91
00:06:37,355 --> 00:06:39,107
We need to break through it.

92
00:06:39,190 --> 00:06:40,733
We can't do that.

93
00:06:40,817 --> 00:06:42,443
- This is too hard.
- We can do it.

94
00:06:42,985 --> 00:06:44,821
We're running out of time.
Let's just blow this up!

95
00:06:44,904 --> 00:06:47,698
No, you can't blow it up.

96
00:06:47,782 --> 00:06:49,909
The tunnel will collapse.
We can't do that.

97
00:06:50,660 --> 00:06:51,911
It's dangerous.

98
00:06:51,994 --> 00:06:53,079
I'm grabbing the dynamite.

99
00:06:54,455 --> 00:06:55,998
Like I said, you can't do that.

100
00:06:56,999 --> 00:06:58,876
Dude, don't do it!

101
00:06:59,877 --> 00:07:01,129
Oh, come on!

102
00:07:01,212 --> 00:07:02,547
I already said no!

103
00:07:02,630 --> 00:07:08,261
[GLUM MUSIC PLAYING]

104
00:07:20,690 --> 00:07:22,108
Boss Emil is on his way here.

105
00:07:22,900 --> 00:07:24,402
Is the tunnel ready?

106
00:07:24,485 --> 00:07:25,695
We're almost done.

107
00:07:28,489 --> 00:07:35,329
[LIGHT FLICKERING]

108
00:07:41,127 --> 00:07:48,050
[GLUM MUSIC CONTINUES]

109
00:07:57,477 --> 00:08:04,442
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

110
00:08:14,785 --> 00:08:18,414
[LIGHT FLICKERING]

111
00:08:18,498 --> 00:08:25,463
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

112
00:08:29,926 --> 00:08:35,973
[GRETA SOBBING]

113
00:08:38,059 --> 00:08:39,018
[LIAM] Ma!

114
00:08:39,101 --> 00:08:41,229
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

115
00:08:41,312 --> 00:08:42,730
Face them.

116
00:08:44,482 --> 00:08:47,443
They're liars. They're all liars!

117
00:08:47,527 --> 00:08:49,946
If that's the case,
why are you running away?

118
00:08:53,533 --> 00:08:56,244
[SOBBING]

119
00:08:56,327 --> 00:08:58,829
Do you believe them, Liam?

120
00:08:58,913 --> 00:09:00,581
Do you believe them?

121
00:09:02,875 --> 00:09:04,001
[GRETA] <i>Jericho?</i>

122
00:09:05,545 --> 00:09:06,587
<i>Who are you talking to?</i>

123
00:09:07,213 --> 00:09:08,673
<i>Who's Jericho?</i>

124
00:09:08,756 --> 00:09:12,218
<i>He's my contact at the police station.</i>

125
00:09:12,301 --> 00:09:13,636
[JERICHO] <i>Listen to your mother!</i>

126
00:09:14,220 --> 00:09:17,056
<i>Greta! Explain everything to your son!</i>

127
00:09:17,139 --> 00:09:19,850
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

128
00:09:19,934 --> 00:09:22,353
<i>He's the mastermind.</i>

129
00:09:22,436 --> 00:09:25,064
<i>The real boss of all of us.</i>

130
00:09:26,732 --> 00:09:28,359
<i>It's not me.</i>

131
00:09:33,823 --> 00:09:36,367
I don't want to believe it, Ma.

132
00:09:37,952 --> 00:09:39,912
But no matter how hard I try,

133
00:09:41,330 --> 00:09:43,291
I can't get it off my mind.

134
00:09:43,374 --> 00:09:45,501
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

135
00:09:45,585 --> 00:09:47,169
What's the truth, Ma?

136
00:09:53,092 --> 00:09:55,970
You told me yourself that
you knew Jacinto.

137
00:09:56,053 --> 00:09:59,515
That you asked him for help
with Roja's security.

138
00:10:00,808 --> 00:10:02,518
But based on what I saw,

139
00:10:04,103 --> 00:10:06,814
when you called him
at the abandoned resort

140
00:10:07,732 --> 00:10:09,734
and we got into a confrontation,

141
00:10:11,360 --> 00:10:13,362
he said you needed to explain something.

142
00:10:13,446 --> 00:10:16,032
And you shot him after he said that.

143
00:10:16,115 --> 00:10:19,535
- [TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]
- [SOBS SHAKILY]

144
00:10:20,578 --> 00:10:22,622
It was because
he was going to kill you, Liam.

145
00:10:24,165 --> 00:10:26,834
Or was it because you didn't want me
to hear what he'd say next?

146
00:10:28,836 --> 00:10:30,004
Tell me the truth.

147
00:10:31,255 --> 00:10:32,715
Well, Ma?

148
00:10:32,798 --> 00:10:34,425
Did you really hear Jacinto say

149
00:10:34,508 --> 00:10:38,387
where he hid the money and jewelry
at the resort?

150
00:10:38,471 --> 00:10:42,266
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

151
00:10:42,350 --> 00:10:43,893
[SOBS]

152
00:10:43,976 --> 00:10:45,603
I already know the truth.

153
00:10:47,063 --> 00:10:48,898
But I need to hear it from you.

154
00:10:50,066 --> 00:10:51,776
Why did you do it?

155
00:10:53,944 --> 00:10:55,446
Why?!

156
00:10:55,529 --> 00:10:56,822
[SOBS] Liam…

157
00:10:57,657 --> 00:10:58,866
I'm sorry.

158
00:11:00,284 --> 00:11:03,287
I was desperate. We're drowning in debt.

159
00:11:04,413 --> 00:11:08,042
Our family's flat-out broke.
I didn't know what to do.

160
00:11:08,125 --> 00:11:11,337
I had no choice.
That was all I could think of.

161
00:11:11,420 --> 00:11:13,839
Do you know how many died because of you?!

162
00:11:13,923 --> 00:11:16,926
So many people died!

163
00:11:17,009 --> 00:11:18,636
This isn't about money, Ma!

164
00:11:19,762 --> 00:11:23,933
This is about lives!
Chief Ben's and our employees'!

165
00:11:24,558 --> 00:11:27,228
- I didn't mean to--
- You made everyone suffer!

166
00:11:27,812 --> 00:11:29,105
I didn't mean to.

167
00:11:29,855 --> 00:11:32,900
I didn't know it would come to this.

168
00:11:32,983 --> 00:11:34,068
You didn't mean to?

169
00:11:34,151 --> 00:11:36,862
Then why did you tell them
not to hurt the hostages

170
00:11:36,946 --> 00:11:38,823
except for Aunt Wendy?

171
00:11:38,906 --> 00:11:43,994
Because what Wendy did to me hurt so much!

172
00:11:44,078 --> 00:11:45,913
And you know that.

173
00:11:45,996 --> 00:11:47,248
Liam.

174
00:11:48,290 --> 00:11:49,708
Liam, please forgive me.

175
00:11:49,792 --> 00:11:51,919
Please forgive me, son.

176
00:11:52,002 --> 00:11:56,674
- [MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [GRETA SOBBING]

177
00:11:57,883 --> 00:12:00,553
I'm not the only one
you should apologize to.

178
00:12:04,723 --> 00:12:06,183
Face them.

179
00:12:07,977 --> 00:12:11,939
[GRETA SOBBING]

180
00:12:12,022 --> 00:12:13,649
- Let's go.
- [FOOTSTEPS THUDDING]

181
00:12:13,732 --> 00:12:19,488
- [MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [GRETA WHIMPERING]

182
00:12:24,201 --> 00:12:30,082
- [TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]
- [SOBBING]

183
00:12:30,166 --> 00:12:32,293
Liam, I don't want to go to jail.

184
00:12:32,376 --> 00:12:34,879
I don't want to go to jail.
I'm begging you!

185
00:12:35,588 --> 00:12:37,339
I'm begging you.

186
00:12:37,423 --> 00:12:39,508
[SOBBING]

187
00:12:39,592 --> 00:12:41,343
Liam.

188
00:12:42,595 --> 00:12:44,638
Liam, I'm begging you.

189
00:12:45,931 --> 00:12:47,808
I don't want to go to jail.

190
00:12:48,559 --> 00:12:51,228
Have mercy on me.

191
00:12:51,812 --> 00:12:53,355
[SOBBING]

192
00:12:53,439 --> 00:12:59,278
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

193
00:12:59,361 --> 00:13:01,238
[REPORTER 1] Let us talk to Mr. Roja.

194
00:13:01,322 --> 00:13:03,616
Please, sir. We'll just ask questions.

195
00:13:03,699 --> 00:13:06,076
We'll just ask questions. That's all.

196
00:13:06,160 --> 00:13:08,579
- [REPORTER 1] Mr. Roja!
- [REPORTER 2] What happened?

197
00:13:08,662 --> 00:13:11,165
- Mr. Roja! Mr. Roja!
- What happened?

198
00:13:11,248 --> 00:13:12,917
- Did anyone die?
- Mr. Roja.

199
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:16,295
Mr. Roja, what can you say about
the accusation against your wife?

200
00:13:16,378 --> 00:13:18,756
Does she really have
something to do with it?

201
00:13:19,507 --> 00:13:20,925
What's going on inside?

202
00:13:21,008 --> 00:13:23,302
- [REPORTER 1] Did anyone die?
- [OFFICER] That's enough.

203
00:13:23,385 --> 00:13:25,679
- [REPORTER 1] Mr. Roja. Wait.
- [REPORTER 3] Did anyone die?

204
00:13:25,763 --> 00:13:27,306
[REPORTER 1] I need to talk to Mr. Roja.

205
00:13:27,389 --> 00:13:29,725
- [REPORTER 1] Mr. Roja! Sir!
- [REPORTER 3] What happened?

206
00:13:29,808 --> 00:13:31,519
[REPORTER 1] Wait, sir!

207
00:13:31,602 --> 00:13:33,979
- [REPORTER 1] Sir! Sir!
- [REPORTER 3] What happened?

208
00:13:34,063 --> 00:13:36,273
- What happened inside?
- Sir!

209
00:13:36,357 --> 00:13:38,776
- Sir!
- [POLICE SIREN HONKS]

210
00:13:38,859 --> 00:13:45,616
[GLUM MUSIC PLAYING]

211
00:13:46,825 --> 00:13:48,869
[MAGNUS] <i>It doesn't matter now.</i>

212
00:13:48,953 --> 00:13:51,247
<i>It matters, Magnus.</i>

213
00:13:51,330 --> 00:13:53,165
<i>You know what matters?</i>

214
00:13:53,249 --> 00:13:56,043
<i>It's the promise we made to each other.</i>

215
00:13:56,126 --> 00:13:59,296
<i>After what happened with Ayen.</i>

216
00:13:59,380 --> 00:14:03,717
<i>We will stick together as a family</i>
<i>no matter what.</i>

217
00:14:04,843 --> 00:14:06,220
<i>That is what matters.</i>

218
00:14:06,303 --> 00:14:09,932
<i>That and our son should be</i>
<i>the only things on your mind.</i>

219
00:14:10,015 --> 00:14:14,186
[GLUM MUSIC CONTINUES]

220
00:14:14,270 --> 00:14:15,479
[MUSIC FADES]

221
00:14:18,649 --> 00:14:23,612
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

222
00:14:23,696 --> 00:14:25,698
I thought you were a goner.

223
00:14:27,366 --> 00:14:29,201
You really didn't leave, huh?

224
00:14:30,327 --> 00:14:31,537
Of course.

225
00:14:31,620 --> 00:14:33,664
I want to help out here.

226
00:14:33,747 --> 00:14:35,624
Yeah, right.

227
00:14:35,708 --> 00:14:37,376
You just can't leave me, can you?

228
00:14:39,461 --> 00:14:41,547
- Ow, ow!
- [IVAN] Ice.

229
00:14:42,548 --> 00:14:45,593
Could you get extra gauze
from the supplies?

230
00:14:45,676 --> 00:14:46,760
Sure.

231
00:14:51,765 --> 00:14:53,183
[ROMANTIC MUSIC PLAYING]

232
00:14:53,267 --> 00:14:54,894
<i>It's not harmful.</i>

233
00:14:54,977 --> 00:14:56,979
<i>Sorry, Ms. Ice, but this isn't</i>
<i>allowed on the premises.</i>

234
00:14:57,062 --> 00:15:00,149
<i>When I come back for it,</i>
<i>you're the one I'll look for.</i>

235
00:15:03,110 --> 00:15:05,070
- <i>Olsen!</i>
- [GRUNTING]

236
00:15:06,030 --> 00:15:07,031
[GUNSHOTS]

237
00:15:08,824 --> 00:15:11,410
<i>Hey, hey, hey.</i>

238
00:15:11,911 --> 00:15:13,245
[OLSEN] <i>Stay strong, okay?</i>

239
00:15:13,871 --> 00:15:15,080
<i>I'll protect you.</i>

240
00:15:15,164 --> 00:15:17,458
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

241
00:15:17,541 --> 00:15:21,420
<i>I'll be here for you, okay?</i>

242
00:15:27,927 --> 00:15:30,804
<i>When I become a resort manager,</i>

243
00:15:30,888 --> 00:15:32,556
<i>I'll hire you as our official nurse.</i>

244
00:15:35,392 --> 00:15:37,937
<i>You know, I was worried sick</i>
<i>about you guys.</i>

245
00:15:39,480 --> 00:15:41,231
<i>I thought we'd never see each other again.</i>

246
00:15:41,857 --> 00:15:43,609
<i>Don't worry, okay?</i>

247
00:15:43,692 --> 00:15:44,568
<i>We'll make it out.</i>

248
00:15:44,652 --> 00:15:50,032
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

249
00:15:58,624 --> 00:16:00,876
- Olsen…
- You're crying again.

250
00:16:01,460 --> 00:16:04,505
I'm fine. I really am.

251
00:16:04,588 --> 00:16:10,678
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

252
00:16:13,931 --> 00:16:17,142
Doc, how is he?

253
00:16:18,060 --> 00:16:22,231
He needs to be monitored
for signs of internal injuries.

254
00:16:22,856 --> 00:16:26,276
But for now, he's in good condition.

255
00:16:29,029 --> 00:16:29,947
[OLSEN] I'm okay.

256
00:16:30,698 --> 00:16:31,824
I promise.

257
00:16:32,533 --> 00:16:34,201
They're just scratches.

258
00:16:34,284 --> 00:16:39,373
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

259
00:16:39,456 --> 00:16:41,083
Where's Magnus?

260
00:16:44,753 --> 00:16:46,547
The police took him.

261
00:16:47,464 --> 00:16:49,550
They think he's Ma'am Greta's accomplice.

262
00:16:51,844 --> 00:16:57,891
Ma, do you think she really
had anything to do with what happened?

263
00:16:58,600 --> 00:17:00,936
There's proof, son.

264
00:17:01,020 --> 00:17:02,855
Proof of her evil.

265
00:17:02,938 --> 00:17:04,231
[LUNA SIGHS]

266
00:17:04,898 --> 00:17:09,445
Even I couldn't believe that
Ma'am Greta could do that.

267
00:17:10,612 --> 00:17:12,197
I was surprised too.

268
00:17:15,951 --> 00:17:18,454
Luna, I thought you were
supposed to have left already?

269
00:17:19,913 --> 00:17:21,290
That's what I was told.

270
00:17:23,083 --> 00:17:26,503
I already told her earlier to go home.

271
00:17:29,048 --> 00:17:30,924
Olsen, I heard

272
00:17:31,008 --> 00:17:33,719
that even Sir Magnus was arrested.

273
00:17:33,802 --> 00:17:35,095
Yes.

274
00:17:35,679 --> 00:17:37,931
We couldn't stop the police.

275
00:17:38,015 --> 00:17:40,559
[SIGHS] What about Liam?

276
00:17:40,642 --> 00:17:42,519
And Ma'am Greta? Where are they?

277
00:17:42,603 --> 00:17:44,313
Greta ran away.

278
00:17:45,397 --> 00:17:48,692
Liam and the police chased her.

279
00:17:49,443 --> 00:17:52,237
She's probably been caught by now.

280
00:17:52,821 --> 00:17:59,787
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

281
00:18:06,001 --> 00:18:07,920
[GRETA BREATHES DEEPLY]

282
00:18:08,670 --> 00:18:12,424
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

283
00:18:12,508 --> 00:18:14,218
[SOBS]

284
00:18:14,301 --> 00:18:15,677
Let's go, Ma.

285
00:18:16,553 --> 00:18:18,472
You need to pay for all of your crimes.

286
00:18:19,681 --> 00:18:21,600
- Come on.
- [WHIMPERS]

287
00:18:21,683 --> 00:18:24,812
[CRIES, SOBS] Liam! No, please.

288
00:18:24,895 --> 00:18:27,648
I can't do it! [SOBS]

289
00:18:27,731 --> 00:18:29,274
[LIAM] I'm not leaving here.

290
00:18:30,317 --> 00:18:32,194
You've already run
from the police once, Ma.

291
00:18:34,488 --> 00:18:36,907
When you pinned your case on Aunt Wendy.

292
00:18:36,990 --> 00:18:38,700
She was in jail for a long time.

293
00:18:40,369 --> 00:18:41,537
You can't escape this anymore.

294
00:18:41,620 --> 00:18:43,831
[CRYING, SOBBING]

295
00:18:43,914 --> 00:18:44,915
Let's go.

296
00:18:45,582 --> 00:18:49,545
[CRYING, SOBBING] I can't do this.

297
00:18:49,628 --> 00:18:54,341
Please! I'm begging you!

298
00:18:54,424 --> 00:19:00,222
[SOBBING, CRYING]

299
00:19:00,305 --> 00:19:02,182
Don't you love me anymore?

300
00:19:03,517 --> 00:19:10,482
- [CRYING, SOBBING]
- [GLUM MUSIC PLAYING]

301
00:19:16,029 --> 00:19:17,906
I'm turning you in to the police

302
00:19:17,990 --> 00:19:19,950
because it's the right thing to do.

303
00:19:21,994 --> 00:19:23,787
That's how you raised me.

304
00:19:23,871 --> 00:19:27,541
[GLUM MUSIC CONTINUES]

305
00:19:27,624 --> 00:19:29,543
It's not that I don't love you.

306
00:19:30,085 --> 00:19:33,338
[SOBBING, CRYING]

307
00:19:33,422 --> 00:19:40,137
[GLUM MUSIC CONTINUES]

308
00:19:43,599 --> 00:19:46,101
<i>Areza, they're in the basement.</i>
<i>In the mechanical room.</i>

309
00:19:46,185 --> 00:19:47,394
<i>Alert all units.</i>

310
00:19:47,477 --> 00:19:49,062
- [DINGS, EXPLOSION]
- [SCREAMING]

311
00:19:49,146 --> 00:19:50,439
<i>Check if the tunnel is passable.</i>

312
00:19:50,522 --> 00:19:52,107
<i>The tunnel could collapse--</i>

313
00:19:52,900 --> 00:19:55,277
<i>There's an opening</i>
<i>leading to the old sewage line.</i>

314
00:19:55,360 --> 00:19:56,653
<i>I'd hurry, starting now.</i>

315
00:19:58,572 --> 00:20:00,657
- [LUCAS]<i> Take cover! Take cover!</i>
- [EMIL] <i>Move!</i>

316
00:20:03,076 --> 00:20:05,746
- [RAPID GUNFIRE]
- [LOUD EXPLOSION]

317
00:20:05,829 --> 00:20:07,998
<i>- You can't turn me in.</i>
<i>- I need to do this. I'm sorry, okay?</i>

318
00:20:08,081 --> 00:20:09,333
<i>- Let's go.</i>
<i>- No! I can't do this!</i>

319
00:20:09,958 --> 00:20:12,836
<i>Let's go somewhere no one knows about.</i>
